# User Manual

- The application starts with the former state restored before of the toDo list. and displays the number of done and undone tasks.

- Then the user has 6 alternatives as a home menu.  The user can choose between alternatives by typing number of alternative from 1 -6. 
To edit a specific task the user needs to input the number of task which stands before the task title. 

- The user can be able to filter tasks according to the project at command 5.
tasks, assign them a title and due date, and choose a project for that task to belong to. The user is able to edit, mark as done or remove tasks. They can also quit and save the current task list to file, and then restart the application with the former state restored.
